# Rules Package

## File Structure

One rule = one file = one test file:

```
packages/rules/src/
  direct-api-in-view.ts
  __tests__/direct-api-in-view.test.ts
  index.ts          # register all rules
```

## Implementation Checklist

Before writing code, read `vue-doctor-rule-writing` and `vue-sfc-ast-analysis` skills.

1. Define exact diagnostic condition (one sentence)
2. Write adversarial tests (valid + invalid + edge cases)
3. Implement detect() using AST only
4. Register in index.ts
5. Run `pnpm test -- --grep "{rule-id}"`

## Anti-patterns

- ❌ `sourceFile.getText().includes('fetch')` — use CallExpression AST
- ❌ Reporting without file + line number
- ❌ Catching all .vue files when rule only applies to views/
- ❌ One mega-file with multiple rules

## Rule Export Pattern

```typescript
import type { Rule } from '@vue-doctor/core';

export const directApiInView: Rule = {
  id: 'direct-api-in-view',
  description: 'API calls should not be made directly in view components',
  severity: 'error',
  category: 'architecture',
  detect(context) {
    // return Issue[]
  },
};
```
